  "detailedRequirements": "<div><strong>Challenge Description:&nbsp;</strong><br />\nIn this challenge we have a couple offline sync items that need to be addressed in an existing Ionic application. See below for details.</div>\n\n<p><strong>Offline Sync</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">The mobile app currently allows a Retailer to add a product to their inventory or sell a product. The app makes a call to the backend and the backend checks if it&rsquo;s a valid product in product catalogue if they are trying to add a product to their inventory. If they are trying to sell a product the backend removes the product from the Retailer inventory.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">There are times when a Retailer might not have an Internet connection so the app needs to have an offline sync feature. The following scenarios relate to the Scan Activity screen when in either &lsquo;Incoming&rsquo; (add to Inventory&rsquo;) or &lsquo;Sold&rsquo; (sell from Inventory) modes.</span></p>\n\n<p><u>Incoming / Sold tabs</u></p>\n\n<p><em>Scenario 1</em><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\"> - The Retailer is a new user that has signed in to the app and then loses Internet connection. They haven&rsquo;t added any products to their inventory yet. In this scenario the Retailer can&rsquo;t scan or manually add any products to the Inventory as he doesn&rsquo;t have an Internet connection. The Retailer cannot sell any products either. Make sure this logic is handled in the app. Display a toast notification on the Scan Activity screen (like the one when a product is successfully scanned i.e. &lsquo;Scan Successful!&rsquo; message) that says &lsquo;No data connection&rsquo;</span></p>\n\n<p><u>Sold tab</u></p>\n\n<p><em>Scenario 2</em><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\"> - The Retailer has signed in to the app. They have added some products to the Inventory. They then lose Internet connection and try to sell a product that is in their Inventory. The app should sync the product offline and when an Internet connection is made sync to the backend.</span></p>\n\n<p><em>Scenario 3</em><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\"> - The Retailer has signed in to the app. They have added some products to the Inventory. They then lose Internet connection and try to sell a product that is </span><strong>not</strong><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\"> in their Inventory. Display a toast message with the message &lsquo;Product not in Inventory&rsquo;.</span></p>\n\n<p><u>Incoming tab</u></p>\n\n<p><em>Scenario 4</em><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\"> - The Retailer has signed in to the app. They have added some products to the Inventory. They then lose Internet connection and try to add a product to their Inventory that is already in their Inventory. The app should sync the product offline and when an Internet connection is made sync to the backend.</span></p>\n\n<p><em>Scenario 5</em><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\"> - The Retailer has signed in to the app. They have added some products to the Inventory. They then lose Internet connection and try to add a product to their Inventory that is </span><strong>not</strong><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\"> in their Inventory. The app should display a the toast message &lsquo;Product not in Inventory. No data connection&rsquo;.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">Note: to work on this feature you will need to use the barcodes in the &lsquo;Barcodes for Testing&rsquo; section of the challenge.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">Please use the &lsquo;clock&rsquo; or the &lsquo;tick&rsquo; symbol to indicate products that have not synced yet versus products that have synced. You&rsquo;ll find these assets in the &lsquo;assets&rsquo; folder of the Gitlab repo.</span></p>\n\n<p><br />\n<span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">\f</span><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/2NZ2V1UiFuKA01A4Fj0brrV3bmnci9eoeq97lV2dEMdUhJBooDBE8SOo6ptEtC4Mwkcw4zeif3NgX8XwuLeH1kbhVNPcu8e0Yd0sdkKr4ge1SCJ6hYQVzF78v3kPqnc3wQrMhHXP\" style=\"-webkit-transform:rotate(0.00rad); border:none; height:544px; transform:rotate(0.00rad); width:329px\" /><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/xIzmUxLGPXYa_RdnVqhARTsTSU4xJ7h_q5RGn3pOcs_Q8AH8y288eZ55PCjOTxhlY1nMoQmC5-7l02AMmiOSirgAFXd2opYypr9E-QTsEM0-eAqDrLM1BcGASYaUA3ZeLUeh0meP\" style=\"-webkit-transform:rotate(0.00rad); border:none; height:558px; transform:rotate(0.00rad); width:338px\" /></p>\n\n<p><br />\n<strong>Barcodes for Testing</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">For the offline sync part of the challenge you&rsquo;ll need some barcodes to test. All of these barcodes exist as valid products in the Retailer Loyalty backend.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/bXjhD3crCwKuvsBe1VGoJDTPU_gv2_yB5qA2u8gZxR7Bet8Ph_jayEqVagBsWTBnkqSQGgLwmsdOseWndD0DqGajZeAxIa997qBqZ8oB4hk8bOYcGGaiS648YxbU_j8wgzFF8NKM\" style=\"-webkit-transform:rotate(0.00rad); border:none; height:120px; transform:rotate(0.00rad); width:246px\" /></span></p>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/5tKe5b4tfcD3ru1QEBstKS1xXCika3w23izxhhqf28JqAsGihkP8YTlQINgrBj3n-RRTFe5gp9Pr-fZwCgxWIpp_JRbSlGZAQkMvhUPeyreIx-sgxko1eF5jq1QjDMUmY0c_EUHK\" style=\"-webkit-transform:rotate(0.00rad); border:none; height:120px; transform:rotate(0.00rad); width:246px\" /></span></p>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\"><img src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/ApWi6amnY4Evp740cwyEtGxIkFB0THLIYEOSJVgGtTuI9nco5m-bkTZf-NA-SCcl1BkOIX7ldm0I2Endysi033XzsMWMsnDixJ6wq_fg-iI3UtHSKSMJDlatJmA1Ep8q07Xl9vVi\" style=\"-webkit-transform:rotate(0.00rad); border:none; height:120px; transform:rotate(0.00rad); width:246px\" /></span></p>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\"><img src=\"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/widcwu9OkD6Bubla4JX1ugSKJ1k25eNWH826bwn-DkGctgqB8AwNGbU5gEWGlkKJGs0mvQQQYoOkvexRalJ3qL-lVrdHxmf-xIVLrALqOLC3YFBsV6c0PaZZdjzWnyGCamVokLl8\" style=\"-webkit-transform:rotate(0.00rad); border:none; height:120px; transform:rotate(0.00rad); width:246px\" /></span></p>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\"><img src=\"https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/UNQ09hF0L5qP5sl_wFB61KH4Ns6UjikOcLOERJNk1i5QXBJ6oNVmo_w_jhJz6sQ_sG5jsTOLHm7qpq_kxXiOU0MYQrz4xaWGNiwlAtIvoLJvpfW07WOpQStJxhwtZzxa5DXDhe1x\" style=\"-webkit-transform:rotate(0.00rad); border:none; height:120px; transform:rotate(0.00rad); width:246px\" /></span></p>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<p><strong>Test Accounts</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">Please use the following test accounts to login as either Retailer or Agent. The password is </span><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:courier new; font-size:13.3333px\">password123</span><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\"> for all accounts. Note: each retailer has been assigned an Agent.</span><br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n\n<div style=\"margin-left:0pt\">\n<p><strong>Retailer &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><strong>Assigned Agent</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">retailer1@example.com &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">agent1@example.com</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">retailer2@example.com &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">agent1@example.com</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">retailer3@example.com &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">agent2@example.com</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">retailer4@example.com &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">agent2@example.com</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">retailer5@example.com &nbsp; &nbsp;</span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">agent3@example.com</span><br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n\n<p><strong>Getting access to the code and building the Ionic app</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">The code for the Ionic app is in a Gitlab repo </span><a href=\"https://gitlab.com/hpe-retailer-loyalty/retailer-loyalty-mobile-app\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\"><u>here</u></a><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">. Ask for access in the forums.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px\">You&rsquo;ll require the following to build the app:</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">NodeJS 6.x or 7.x</span><br />\n<span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">Ionic 2.1.x</span><br />\n<span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">Cordova 6+</span><br />\n<span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">Android SDK (latest updates)</span><br />\n<span style=\"background-color:transparent; font-size:14.6667px\">Java 8</span></p>\n\n<ul>\n</ul>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">Once you have cloned the repo you must work off the &lsquo;develop&rsquo; branch.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">Run the following commands (make sure you&rsquo;re in the &lsquo;ionic&rsquo; directory).</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"background-color:rgb(249, 242, 244); color:rgb(199, 37, 78); font-family:courier new; font-size:13.3333px\">$ npm i</span><br />\n<span style=\"background-color:rgb(249, 242, 244); color:rgb(199, 37, 78); font-family:courier new; font-size:13.3333px\">$ ionic state restore</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">To run in browser:</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"background-color:rgb(249, 242, 244); color:rgb(199, 37, 78); font-family:courier new; font-size:13.3333px\">ionic serve</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">To run in connected android device:</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"background-color:rgb(249, 242, 244); color:rgb(199, 37, 78); font-family:courier new; font-size:13.3333px\">ionic run android</span><br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n\n<div><strong>About this challenge:</strong></div>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">Welcome to the Retailer Loyalty Mobile App Challenge. Our client is a leading agriculture company that supplies its products to Retailers. Visibility into retailer inventory and their sales of our clients products is very limited and the process is manual. &nbsp;Retailers receive our client&#39;s products but do not report back on actual sales nor inventory. &nbsp;There is also no formal loyalty process that includes retailers.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">The Agriculture company supplies products like Fertilizer, Herbicide, Pesticide, Fungicide, Plant Tonic.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">We have built a a mobile application for Android using Ionic 2 to automate this Retailer Loyalty process. The app will adds value in facilitating the Retailer on-boarding process, update product inventory at point of sale and encourage retailers to engage with our client in the form of a Retailer Loyalty feature.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:13.3333px\">The app enables the clients Sales agents to engage with their retailers, view specific data related to each retailer, and gain valuable insight into actual products sold. &nbsp;Our clients Sales agents can further engage with the retailer via the Retailer Loyalty feature.</span></p>\n",
